\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering API extension**\\n\\nI need to think about whether to add a class that extends AutoDerivation. This could allow users to mix it into helpers, which is interesting. However, the user mentioned not to retest logic flows that are already present, and I'm concerned this might duplicate what's already happening with auto derivation. I'll have to weigh the pros and cons of integrating this to make sure it aligns with the user's intentions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Scala implicit behavior**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether Scala implicit can resolve to the same given, especially through recursive derivation. I think testing it could help clarify if inline works. The Circe documentation might have context on recursive ADTs, and I could manually separate the codec derivations. \\n\\nIt seems like using `lazy given` could pose a risk of compile failure, especially with recursive case classes. When working with field derivatives like `List[Category]`, I have to be cautious about cyclic initialization. Would defining `codec = semiauto.deriveCodec[Tree]` work at runtime?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mxyYsaW483TwHwOdxjBqHd4o|fc_093898a9c14b051c016a28d295f514819591219e401107da89", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nfor path in [\n'modules/core/shared/src/main/scala-3/io/circe/derivation/ConfiguredEncoder.scala',\n'modules/core/shared/src/main/scala-3/io/circe/Encoder.scala',\n'modules/core/shared/src/main/scala-3/io/circe/derivation/derives.scala',\n]:\n  url='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/circe/circe/v0.14.12/'+path\n  try:\n    txt=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=10).read().decode()\n    print('---',path, len(txt)); print(txt[:3000])\n  except Exception as e: print('ERR',path,e)\nPY", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1659, "output": 1649, "cacheRead": 22528, "c